  "plain_language_assessment": "M5m still does not prove whole-Flye acceleration. Its CUDA-side benefit is integration proof: a verified GPU-derived GraphAlignment object vector replaced a tiny selected _readAlignments slice, Flye consumed that substituted vector, and the final canonical assembly artifacts stayed identical to the CPU baseline. The run is not faster because CPU read alignment is still computed first for oracle gating.",
